How is it?

7
00:00:47,881 --> 00:00:49,415
What do you think.

8
00:00:49,416 --> 00:00:51,750
I need it for
the drama next week

9
00:00:51,751 --> 00:00:53,185
so tell him it's great!

10
00:00:53,186 --> 00:00:55,020
Like Seung-chul ever listens to me.

11
00:00:55,021 --> 00:00:58,323
Then make him.
He's gotta do this song.

12
00:00:58,324 --> 00:01:01,635
But the lyrics are weak, man.

13
00:01:01,761 --> 00:01:04,229
What the suits say goes.
That's show biz.

14
00:01:04,230 --> 00:01:06,232
Whatever, man!

15
00:01:06,399 --> 00:01:08,100
- Hold up!
- What is it?

16
00:01:08,101 --> 00:01:09,234
You like this song?

17
00:01:09,235 --> 00:01:10,469
Of course! Why?

18
00:01:10,470 --> 00:01:14,073
Singing about a girl
to come back to me at my age?

19
00:01:14,074 --> 00:01:16,775
My heart this and
tears that...

20
00:01:16,776 --> 00:01:17,776
Isn't it childish?

21
00:01:17,777 --> 00:01:21,046
No! It's perfect!
Don't you think?

22
00:01:21,047 --> 00:01:21,747
It's great.

23
00:01:21,748 --> 00:01:23,982
Make your fans
really feel the song, man!

24
00:01:23,983 --> 00:01:25,984
But I don't feel anything!

25
00:01:25,985 --> 00:01:29,688
You can do it, man.
Feel me?

26
00:01:29,689 --> 00:01:30,689
- It's great!
- No.

27
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:32,692
It's not working for me.

28
00:01:35,261 --> 00:01:37,096
Seung-chul! Come on!

29
00:01:37,097 --> 00:01:39,441
Get him!

30
00:01:39,532 --> 00:01:40,840
Seung-chul!

31
00:01:41,101 --> 00:01:42,512
Yes, director.

32
00:01:42,869 --> 00:01:44,314
I see.

33
00:01:44,504 --> 00:01:45,571
<i>KWON Sang-woo</i>

34
00:01:45,572 --> 00:01:47,643
<i>KWON</i> Sang-woo
Next Tuesday?

35
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:50,476
The song's a killer.

36
00:01:50,477 --> 00:01:51,110
<i>LEE Bo-young</i>

37
00:01:51,111 --> 00:01:53,112
<i>LEE</i> Bo-young Nothing but the
best from LEE Seung-chul.

38
00:01:53,113 --> 00:01:54,353
Nothing but the best
from LEE Seung-chul.

39
00:01:54,747 --> 00:01:56,281
Of course.

40
00:01:56,282 --> 00:01:57,216
<i>LEE Beom-soo</i>

41
00:01:57,217 --> 00:02:00,323
<i>LEE</i> Beom-soo
No problems whatsoever.

42
00:02:01,688 --> 00:02:02,554
Yes, sir. Take care.

43
00:02:02,555 --> 00:02:04,256
<i>JUNG Ae-yeon, LEE Han-wui
Yes, sir. Take</i> care.

44
00:02:04,257 --> 00:02:05,702
<i>JUNG Ae-yeon, LEE Han-wui</i>

45
00:02:06,993 --> 00:02:07,960
See? He's asking for the song.
Do it for me?

46
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:11,499
Executive Producer KIM Gwang-soo See?
He's asking for the song. Do it for me?

47
00:02:11,798 --> 00:02:15,167
You always do this to me.

48
00:02:15,168 --> 00:02:16,869
Please?

49
00:02:16,870 --> 00:02:18,537
So get me a good song
and I'll sing it! Damn!

50
00:02:18,538 --> 00:02:18,837
Producer HONG Jung-pyo So get me a
good song and I'll sing it! Damn!

51
00:02:18,838 --> 00:02:22,752
Producer HONG Jung-pyo So get me a
good song and I'll sing it! Damn!

52
00:02:22,842 --> 00:02:24,810
What about 'Hee-ya'?

53
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:26,445
'Hee-ya, please look at me.'

54
00:02:26,446 --> 00:02:28,080
Give me a break.

55
00:02:28,081 --> 00:02:30,716
That was a hit
only because you sang it.

56
00:02:30,717 --> 00:02:33,252
Wanna hear this song I got?

57
00:02:33,253 --> 00:02:34,353
What is it?

58
00:02:34,354 --> 00:02:36,755
It's off a flopped album.

59
00:02:36,756 --> 00:02:38,957
Forget it, kid!

60
00:02:38,958 --> 00:02:41,260
Let's hear it.

61
00:02:41,261 --> 00:02:43,537
Really? Turn it on.

62
00:02:45,598 --> 00:02:51,446
<i>To give you everything
and all my love...</i>

63
00:02:51,538 --> 00:02:54,339
Who wrote this?
The lyrics are great.

64
00:02:54,340 --> 00:02:58,049
Really? Then let's ask them
to write our lyrics.

65
00:02:58,278 --> 00:02:59,645
Who wrote this?

66
00:02:59,646 --> 00:03:03,115
Not sure.
I got this off someone.

67
00:03:03,116 --> 00:03:03,916
Who?

68
00:03:03,917 --> 00:03:06,451
Min-chul. He used to work for
KIM Gap-sik.

69
00:03:06,452 --> 00:03:08,693
Gap-sik?
I know him well.

70
00:03:09,789 --> 00:03:13,737
Hey, didn't he leave the biz?

71
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:14,993
Who does your friend
work for now?

72
00:03:14,994 --> 00:03:17,262
He left the biz, too.

73
00:03:17,263 --> 00:03:18,297
What does he do?

74
00:03:18,298 --> 00:03:20,505
He runs a cafe in Chung-pyung.

75
00:03:21,301 --> 00:03:23,406
Wanna go over, Seung-chul?

76
00:03:23,536 --> 00:03:25,880
- Know where it is?
- Yes.

77
00:03:25,972 --> 00:03:26,672
Lead the way.

78
00:03:26,673 --> 00:03:29,244
<i>Director WON</i>

79
00:03:33,012 --> 00:03:34,116
Got the album?

80
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:35,454
Ah, here.

81
00:03:38,084 --> 00:03:39,529
What's the title?

82
00:03:39,652 --> 00:03:41,427
It's the second track.

83
00:03:42,222 --> 00:03:43,997
Second track?

84
00:03:47,327 --> 00:03:51,530
'No one else like Thee'
by Cream?

85
00:03:51,531 --> 00:03:52,942
What's her real name?

86
00:03:53,032 --> 00:03:57,879
I think it was EUN Won.
Yeah, that' s it.

87
00:03:58,104 --> 00:03:59,879
Got her number?

88
00:04:00,506 --> 00:04:01,506
She's gone.

89
00:04:01,507 --> 00:04:03,809
Gone? To where?

90
00:04:03,810 --> 00:04:06,478
Right after KANG Chul-kyu left...

91
00:04:06,479 --> 00:04:10,655
KANG knows her well?

92
00:04:11,551 --> 00:04:15,624
Of course.
He was totally in love with her.

93
00:04:16,489 --> 00:04:19,129
Do you have KANG's number?

94
00:04:19,892 --> 00:04:21,769
- He died.
- He's dead?

95
00:04:21,828 --> 00:04:23,128
When?

96
00:04:23,129 --> 00:04:26,633
About a month after
he married off EUN Won.

97
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,776
Mr. KANG!

98
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:33,342
What was the name of his show?

99
00:04:33,439 --> 00:04:35,407
'Ugly Ducklings in Love'.

100
00:04:35,408 --> 00:04:37,743
Yeah, that's it!

101
00:04:37,744 --> 00:04:40,946
He married off
the woman he loved?

102
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:43,826
- What does that mean?
- Well...

103
00:04:44,751 --> 00:04:48,062
Tell us what happened.

104
00:04:48,688 --> 00:04:51,430
It's a long story.

105
00:05:41,841 --> 00:05:43,149
Hi, Chul-kyu!

106
00:05:56,789 --> 00:05:59,235
<i>KANG said he saw stars</i>

107
00:05:59,325 --> 00:06:00,592
<i>when he first met Cream.</i>

108
00:06:00,593 --> 00:06:02,595
Why you little punk!

109
00:06:08,568 --> 00:06:11,048
<i>Like he'd been slapped
on the back of his head.</i>

110
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:14,274
<i>He said it was love
at first sight.</i>

111
00:06:15,174 --> 00:06:17,120
<i>Without even talking to her.</i>

112
00:06:18,211 --> 00:06:19,815
<i>I asked,</i>

113
00:06:19,979 --> 00:06:22,789
<i>'Shouldn't you at least
say a few words, first?'</i>

114
00:06:22,949 --> 00:06:24,485
<i>Then he said...</i>

115
00:06:25,351 --> 00:06:29,390
<i>If you need words,
then how can mutes love?</i>

116
00:06:43,269 --> 00:06:46,705
How did you know my name?

117
00:06:46,706 --> 00:06:50,950
Isn't it a waste living
in this big place alone?

118
00:06:53,513 --> 00:06:55,754
Want me to live with you?

119
00:07:12,265 --> 00:07:16,401
Think of a name for me,
and I'll make one for you.

120
00:07:16,402 --> 00:07:18,507
We can't change our names.

121
00:07:19,372 --> 00:07:20,407
Why not?

122
00:07:20,473 --> 00:07:23,886
<i>Her name is Cream
and my name is K.</i>

123
00:07:24,043 --> 00:07:26,778
<i>She was cold like ice cream,</i>

124
00:07:26,779 --> 00:07:29,581
- but <i>also</i> sweet <i>like</i> ice cream.
- The curtains won't do.

125
00:07:29,582 --> 00:07:30,782
We're changing everything.

126
00:07:30,783 --> 00:07:33,389
<i>And she was
soft like ice cream.</i>

127
00:07:34,420 --> 00:07:39,699
And I'm not
A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H, I, J, <i>K...</i>

128
00:07:40,059 --> 00:07:41,766
<i>But just K.</i>

129
00:07:55,575 --> 00:07:57,714
<i>We had a lot in common.</i>

130
00:07:58,110 --> 00:08:02,149
<i>We were the same age.
We both liked noodles.</i>

131
00:08:04,116 --> 00:08:06,824
<i>We loved listening to music
on rainy days.</i>

132
00:08:08,521 --> 00:08:10,728
<i>We loved coffee.</i>

133
00:08:13,693 --> 00:08:15,502
<i>We hated school.</i>

134
00:08:19,999 --> 00:08:21,808
<i>She liked me.</i>

135
00:08:22,902 --> 00:08:24,813
<i>And I liked her.</i>

136
00:08:26,973 --> 00:08:28,884
<i>And we were both orphans.</i>

137
00:08:32,278 --> 00:08:34,312
<i>Prison and love...</i>

138
00:08:34,313 --> 00:08:37,192
<i>Once you're stuck,
you can't get out.</i>

139
00:08:41,787 --> 00:08:45,360
<i>I fell in love with Cream.</i>

140
00:08:48,327 --> 00:08:51,171
<i>Even the very air she breathed.</i>

141
00:08:57,737 --> 00:09:00,581
<i>Romeo must've been so worried...</i>

142
00:09:00,806 --> 00:09:05,619
<i>loving Juliet,
but afraid he might lose her.</i>

143
00:09:10,383 --> 00:09:13,796
<i>Why did he drink the poison?</i>

144
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:18,362
<i>Perhaps he knew.</i>

145
00:09:19,592 --> 00:09:22,160
<i>To love someone</i>

146
00:09:22,161 --> 00:09:24,402
<i>- is to give her everything.</i>
- I'll visit <i>often.</i>

147
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:33,912
<i>I</i> received so much from her
like the catcher who gets the ball'.

148
00:09:35,408 --> 00:09:38,276
<i>Love was like dry ice.
Sometimes cold, sometimes hot.</i>

149
00:09:38,277 --> 00:09:39,347
Wait!

150
00:09:39,478 --> 00:09:41,287
<i>Cream was so loveable.</i>

151
00:09:42,848 --> 00:09:49,060
<i>But I couldn't tell her
that I loved her.</i>

152
00:09:50,456 --> 00:09:57,704
<i>Because I had cancer cells in me
ready to strike at any time.</i>

153
00:10:00,466 --> 00:10:06,212
<i>More than Blue</i>

154
00:10:43,609 --> 00:10:45,176
Thank you, Mr. KIM.

155
00:10:45,177 --> 00:10:48,647
It's the least I can do.

156
00:10:48,648 --> 00:10:52,017
Writers need to eat well
to do all that thinking.

157
00:10:52,018 --> 00:10:57,018
Have some soup with the Kimbap
and chew carefully.

158
00:10:57,556 --> 00:10:59,658
Is this your new singer?

159
00:10:59,659 --> 00:11:06,099
Greet them, girl.
They're the best writers in SBC.

160
00:11:06,832 --> 00:11:11,403
Hello, I'm Cat Girl.
I promise to sing my heart out.

161
00:11:11,404 --> 00:11:13,611
Damn right you should.

162
00:11:14,106 --> 00:11:15,940
Great outfit.

163
00:11:15,941 --> 00:11:19,047
It's a new concept.
She's a cat.

164
00:11:19,979 --> 00:11:21,346
It's Cat Girl.

165
00:11:21,347 --> 00:11:25,817
This gal's got brains.

166
00:11:25,818 --> 00:11:28,920
She's a student
at Seoul University.

167
00:11:28,921 --> 00:11:30,594
Really?

168
00:11:31,290 --> 00:11:33,925
It's Seoul University of Arts.

169
00:11:33,926 --> 00:11:35,963
Whose side are you on?

170
00:11:36,095 --> 00:11:38,730
You could get in trouble
for lying about schools these days.

171
00:11:38,731 --> 00:11:43,234
If you're so holy,
go be a cop instead.

172
00:11:43,235 --> 00:11:44,305
Sorry.

173
00:11:47,606 --> 00:11:48,983
Mr. Kang!

174
00:11:49,075 --> 00:11:49,974
How are you?

175
00:11:49,975 --> 00:11:54,185
Here's Seung-chuFs new album.
It's deep.

176
00:11:54,647 --> 00:11:57,782
- It's a sure hit.
- I'm sure it's great.

177
00:11:57,783 --> 00:11:58,850
- Say hi.
- Hello.

178
00:11:58,851 --> 00:12:00,125
Call me K.

179
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,487
Let's go for drinks some time.

180
00:12:02,488 --> 00:12:04,229
- Sounds great.
- Bye.

181
00:12:05,758 --> 00:12:08,093
Seoul Univ. of Arts.
Same difference.

182
00:12:08,094 --> 00:12:09,394
That's right.

183
00:12:09,395 --> 00:12:10,840
Did you eat, sir?

184
00:12:11,464 --> 00:12:12,831
Mr. Kang!

185
00:12:12,832 --> 00:12:15,133
- How've you been?
- I waited so long for you.

186
00:12:15,134 --> 00:12:18,803
She's Cats.
Damn, I keep forgetting.

187
00:12:18,804 --> 00:12:20,909
It's Cat Girl, sir.

188
00:12:21,073 --> 00:12:24,816
Go on and
introduce yourself, girl.

189
00:12:24,944 --> 00:12:29,714
I'm Cat Girl.
I promise to sing my heart out.

190
00:12:29,715 --> 00:12:30,882
Thank you.

191
00:12:30,883 --> 00:12:33,557
Of course you should.

192
00:12:33,819 --> 00:12:36,788
Let's go some place quiet
to talk, Mr. Kang.

193
00:12:36,789 --> 00:12:39,133
See you folks later.

194
00:12:40,626 --> 00:12:43,928
- Come on, what are pals for.
- I can't.

195
00:12:43,929 --> 00:12:47,877
It's just a show
of my appreciation.

196
00:12:47,967 --> 00:12:49,667
The album's finished?

197
00:12:49,668 --> 00:12:53,371
I put together all the best
songwriters around.

198
00:12:53,372 --> 00:12:56,615
You know me,
I get what I want.

199
00:12:56,942 --> 00:12:58,276
How is she?

200
00:12:58,277 --> 00:13:01,780
Oh, her?
Not bad.

201
00:13:01,781 --> 00:13:05,784
But she has trouble
getting along with the others.

202
00:13:05,785 --> 00:13:08,119
Still she's got talent.
Be nice.

203
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:11,727
Of course.
Anything for you.

204
00:13:13,292 --> 00:13:15,960
- But do this for me.
- I can't.

205
00:13:15,961 --> 00:13:18,464
It's not much.
Please, take it!

206
00:13:18,864 --> 00:13:23,864
I can't sleep
at the thought of you.

207
00:13:25,704 --> 00:13:31,086
My dear love.

208
00:13:33,112 --> 00:13:38,112
That part you just sang.
Try not to scream it this time.

209
00:13:38,584 --> 00:13:40,586
You'll scare 'em off.

210
00:13:41,453 --> 00:13:44,229
How, sir?

211
00:13:45,491 --> 00:13:50,941
How would you feel
if someone screamed they loved you?

212
00:13:51,230 --> 00:13:56,612
You know, softly and tenderly?
You're good at that.

213
00:13:56,702 --> 00:14:01,310
What? Not that.
Stop making me do it.

214
00:14:01,440 --> 00:14:06,048
- That's not what I meant!
- Roll it!

215
00:14:15,054 --> 00:14:17,432
What's she so good at?

216
00:14:17,857 --> 00:14:21,430
Drop it will ya, man?

217
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:24,871
Come on.
Just between us?

218
00:14:28,033 --> 00:14:33,312
She's my future.
That's all I can tell ya, man.

219
00:14:35,608 --> 00:14:38,987
Did you fix the second verse?

220
00:14:39,111 --> 00:14:40,590
What?

221
00:14:40,913 --> 00:14:43,325
The climax on the second verse.

222
00:14:43,482 --> 00:14:45,758
'Always like yesterday'?

223
00:14:45,918 --> 00:14:49,024
It's a little corny,
isn't it?

224
00:14:50,256 --> 00:14:53,931
'A world without love?'
How's that?

225
00:14:56,896 --> 00:14:59,934
Like that's not corny?

226
00:15:02,468 --> 00:15:05,779
It's just a suggestion.

227
00:15:05,871 --> 00:15:12,880
Let's not get too excited here.

228
00:15:17,149 --> 00:15:20,528
You two write it, then.
I'm out.

229
00:15:21,220 --> 00:15:22,597
What?

230
00:15:26,992 --> 00:15:28,835
So feisty.

231
00:15:52,718 --> 00:15:54,595
Do you have to become a singer?

232
00:15:55,554 --> 00:15:57,090
What?

233
00:16:02,161 --> 00:16:04,505
Got enough medication left?

234
00:16:18,577 --> 00:16:22,184
My damn connection
to your family.

235
00:16:26,452 --> 00:16:29,524
First your father, now you.

236
00:16:31,323 --> 00:16:34,429
There are too many illnesses
that can't be cured.

237
00:16:53,379 --> 00:16:54,687
What's wrong?

238
00:16:59,752 --> 00:17:01,060
What is it?

239
00:17:03,789 --> 00:17:05,268
Don't cry.

240
00:17:06,258 --> 00:17:07,794
Stop crying-

241
00:17:09,228 --> 00:17:12,232
The bastards told me
to rewrite it.

242
00:17:17,936 --> 00:17:21,941
'If I could live again'.
How's that for the title?

243
00:17:22,741 --> 00:17:25,085
'If I could live again?'

244
00:17:25,844 --> 00:17:31,089
If you could,
what would you like to be reborn as?

245
00:17:32,351 --> 00:17:34,228
Besides a person?

246
00:17:35,254 --> 00:17:36,961
Anything.

247
00:17:39,224 --> 00:17:41,135
Well...

248
00:17:42,761 --> 00:17:45,037
lf l could live again...

249
00:17:47,966 --> 00:17:49,267
A ring?

250
00:17:49,268 --> 00:17:50,679
Wait.

251
00:17:58,410 --> 00:18:00,014
Start over.

252
00:18:02,548 --> 00:18:04,755
If I could be born again...

253
00:18:05,484 --> 00:18:07,327
